    <Object Type="Vector.CANalyzer.Panels.Design.StaticTextControl, Vector.CANalyzer.Panels.CommonControls, Version=17.3.40.0, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=null" Name="StaticTextControl2" Children="Controls" ControlName="Static Text">
      <Property Name="Name">StaticTextControl2</Property>
      <Property Name="Size">505, 351</Property>
      <Property Name="Location">19, 248</Property>
      <Property Name="BackColor">HighlightText</Property>
      <Property Name="Text">The signals are used as follows:

Channel 01 is an output that generates a signal depending on the button labelled 'CANoe Start'.
This signal indicates an active CANoe session.
It also controls the 'traffic light' style status display.

Channel 02 is an output that generates a signal depending on the button labelled 'DUT Start'.
This signal is used to show the state (active or idle) of the DUT.
It also controls the 'traffic light' style status display.

Channel 03 is an input that is used to detect the signal from the button labelled 'DUT Start'.
It detects a positive edge of the button signal. The CANoe state must be running in order to start the DUT!

Channel 05 is an input that is used to measure the duty cycle of the 'PWM dimmable LED'.

Channel 06 is an input that uses Bit0 of the counter to calculate the counter frequency.

Channels 09..11 are inputs used to measure the bits of the 4-bit counter of the DUT.
They are used to calculate the counter value that is displayed on the CANoe panel.

Channel 14 is an input that is used to measure the duty cycle of the distance signal.
This signal is coded as follows: 1cm = 1% duty cycle ... 100cm = 100% duty cycle.

Channel 15 is an input that is used to measure the rpms of the fan on the DUT.

Channel 16 is an output that is used to control the speed of the fan on the DUT.
This signal is a PWM signal that directly drives the fan.
</Property>
    </Object>
